#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:10
msgid ""
"From OTRS 2.0 on, Access Control Lists (ACLs) can be used to control access "
"to tickets, modules, queues, etc., or to influence actions on tickets "
"(closing, moving, etc.) in certain situations. ACLs can be used to "
"supplement the existing permission system of <link linkend=\"adminarea-roles"
"\">roles</link> and <link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">groups</link>.  Using "
"ACLs, rudimentary work-flows within the system can be mapped, based on "
"ticket attributes."
msgstr ""
"从OTRS 2.0开始，访问控制列表（ACL）能用来控制到工单、模块、队列等的访问权限，"
"或在某些状况下影响工单操作（关闭、转移等）。ACL可以作为现有系统权限<link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-roles\">角色</link>和<link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">"
"组</link>的补充。使用ACL在系统中映射基本的基于工单属性的工作流。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:19
msgid ""
"In a general way ACLs are used to reduce the possible options for a ticket "
"based on a defined set of rules."
msgstr "一般来说，ACL用基于一个预定义的规则集来减少一个工单可能的选项。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:23
msgid ""
"ACLs can be directly entered into the <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</filename> "
"file.  However this is not any more recommended as OTRS comes now with a GUI "
"<link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">Access Control Lists</link> in the Admin "
"panel that allows to save the ACLs in the Database as the first step and "
"then deploy them into a file when they are ready."
msgstr ""
"ACL定义可以直接写入文件 <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</filename>。但是现在不再推"
"荐这种方式，因为在系统管理面板<link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">Access "
"Control Lists访问控制列表</link>图形界面允许首先将ACL保存到数据库中，然后在准"
"备使用时部署到一个文件。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:31
msgid ""
"This chapter has some ACL examples which will walk you through the process "
"of defining ACL definitions, and a reference of all possible important ACL "
"settings."
msgstr ""
"本章有一些ACL示例可以帮助你熟悉定义ACL的流程，还有ACL所有可能重要的设置的参考"
"说明。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><warning><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:36
msgid "The default user 'root@localhost' is not affected by the Ticket ACLs"
msgstr "默认用户‘root@localhost’不受工单ACL的影响。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:41
msgid "Definition"
msgstr "定义"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:43
msgid ""
"The ACL definition can be split into two big parts, 'Matching' and 'Change'. "
"In the matching sections the ACLs contains attributes that has to be met in "
"order to use the ACL. If the attributes defined in the ACL does not match "
"with the attributes that are sent, then the ACL does not take any affect, "
"but any other match ACL will. The change sections contains the rules to "
"reduce the possible options for a ticket."
msgstr ""
"ACL定义可以拆分为两大部分：‘匹配’和‘修改’。在ACL匹配部分包含用来满足使用ACL的"
"属性，如果ACL中定义的属性不匹配传递过来的属性，则ACL不会产生任何影响，但匹配"
"了ACL就会产生影响。修改部分包含减少工单可能选项的规则。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:50
msgid "Matching Sections"
msgstr "匹配部分"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:52
msgid "Properties"
msgstr "属性"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:54
msgid ""
"This section contains matching options that can be changed on the fly. For "
"example on a ticket creation time the data of the ticket changes dynamically "
"as the agent sets the information. If an ACL is set to match a ticket "
"attribute then only when the matching attribute is selected the ACL will be "
"active and might reduce other ticket attributes, but as soon as another "
"value is selected the ACL will not take any affect."
msgstr ""
"本部分包含可动态修改的匹配选项。例如：在一个工单创建时随着服务人员设置工单信"
"息而动态修改工单数据。如果一条ACL匹配了一个工单属性，则只有当匹配的属性被选择"
"时ACL将会激活并可能减少其它的工单属性，但只要选择了另一个值，ACL就不会产生任"
"何影响。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:63
msgid "PropertiesDatabase"
msgstr "PropertiesDatabase数据库中的属性"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:65
msgid ""
"This section is similar to <literal>Properties</literal> but does not take "
"changes in ticket attributes that are not saved into the DataBase, this "
"means that changing an attribute without submit will not make any effect. "
"This section is not use for ticket creation screens (as tickets are not yet "
"created in the Database)."
msgstr ""
"本部分类似于<literal>属性</literal>，但不会更改未保存到数据库中的工单属性，这"
"意味着更改属性而不提交将不会产生任何影响。 本部分内容不用于创建工单屏幕（因为"
"工单尚未在数据库中创建）。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:73
msgid "Change Sections"
msgstr "更改部分"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:75
msgid "Possible"
msgstr "Possible（可能的）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:77
msgid ""
"Possible section resets the data to be reduce to only the elements that are "
"set in this section."
msgstr "‘可能的’部分重置数据，以便将数据减少为只有在本部分列出的元素。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:82
msgid "PossibleAdd"
msgstr "PossibleAdd（添加可能的）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:84
msgid ""
"Elements in PossibleAdd section add missing elements that were reduced in "
"other ACLs. PossibleAdd is only used in together with other ACLs that have "
"Possible or PossibleNot sections."
msgstr ""
"在‘添加可能的’部分的元素添加因在其它ACL减少而缺失的元素。‘添加可能的’只能连同"
"其它有‘可能的’或‘不可能的’部分的ACL使用。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:90
msgid "PossibleNot"
msgstr "PossibleNot（不可能的）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:92
msgid ""
"This section is used to remove specific elements from the current data.  It "
"could be used stand alone or together with other ACLs with a Possible or "
"PossibleAdd sections."
msgstr ""
"本部分用于从当前数据中移除特定元素。它可以单独使用，也可以与连同其它有‘可能"
"的’或‘添加可能的’部分的ACL使用。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:99
msgid ""
"In order to make the development of ACLs easier and more powerful there is a "
"set of so called modifiers for the attributes on each section. This "
"modifiers are explained below:"
msgstr ""
"为了使ACL的开发更容易且更强大，每个部分还有一些所谓的属性‘修改器’。这个修改器"
"的解释如下："

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:103
msgid "Modifiers"
msgstr "修改器"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:105
msgid "[Not]"
msgstr "[Not]非"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:107
msgid ""
"This modifier is used to negate a value for example: '[Not]2 low' in this "
"case talking about ticket priorities will be the same as to have: '1 very "
"low', '3 normal', '4 high', '5 very high'."
msgstr ""
"这个修改器用来取反一个值，例如：有关工单优先级的'[Not]2-低'，与以下结果相"
"同：'1-非常低'、 '3-正常'、 '4-高'、 '5-非常高'。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:113
msgid "[RegExp]"
msgstr "[RegExp]正则表达式（区分大小写）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:115
msgid ""
"It is use to define a regular expression for matching several values, for "
"example '[RegExp]low' talking about priorities is the same as '1 very low', "
"'2 low'."
msgstr ""
"用来定义一个正则表达式以匹配多个值，例如：关于工单优先级的 '[RegExp]low'就是 "
"'1 very low'、 '2 low'。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:121
msgid "[regexp]"
msgstr "[regexp]正则表达式（忽略大小写）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:122
msgid "It is very similar to [RegExp] but it is case insensitive."
msgstr "它与[RegExp]正则表达式（区分大小写）很相似，但它是不区分大小写的。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:125
msgid "[NotRegExp]"
msgstr "[NotRegExp]-正则表达式取反"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:127
msgid ""
"Negated regular expressions for example '[NotRegExp]low' talking about "
"priorities is the same as '3 normal', '4 high', '5 very high'."
msgstr ""
"对正则表达式取反，如关于工单优先级的'[NotRegExp]低'就相当于是'3-正常'、'4-"
"高'、'5-非常高'。"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:132
msgid "[Notregexp]"
msgstr "[Notregexp]-正则表达式取反（忽略大小写）"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/customization/acl.xml:133
msgid "It is very similar to [NotRegExp] but it is case insensitive."
msgstr "它与[NotRegExp]-正则表达式取反很相似，但它是不区分大小写的。"

